<item>
            <title>[LU-8038] lfs migrate fails with --block option</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8038</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Lustre will acquire a group lock while &apos;lfs migrate --block&apos; running. But the CBPENDING flag will cause a new group lock be created against same file. This issue exists a long time. It was revealed by change &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/16456/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/16456/&lt;/a&gt; and fixed by &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/17838/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/17838/&lt;/a&gt;. So we should add a test case for &apos;lfs migrate --block&apos; to avoid such issue lurking again.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
